{"questionId":"10493","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Dinitrogen monoxide, N<sub>2</sub>O, causes depletion of ozone in the stratosphere.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The Lewis (electron dot) structure of the dinitrogen monoxide molecule can be represented as:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/20fd4e8e378c122c596c62550fe3d70a9d962fe4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"373\" height=\"54\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">State what the presence of alternative Lewis structures shows about the nature of the bonding in the molecule.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">delocalization</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">OR</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">delocalized <em>π</em>-electrons &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note: </strong>Accept “resonance”.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10493","referenceCode":"19M.2.hl.TZ2.3d(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State what the presence of alternative Lewis structures shows about the nature of the bonding in the molecule.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 14: Chemical bonding and structure","14.1 Covalent bonding and electron domain and molecular geometries","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 14: Chemical bonding and structure"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}